The paper focuses on the development of a robotic system that can interpret its perceptions in order to perform tasks in a non-controlled environment. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper specifically addresses the challenges of vision-based interpretation, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to build a representation of the environment, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of interactive perception, which is a technique used in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
